<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1803" box="[721,791,824,849]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Ledra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[721,791,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Ledra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Legs imperfectly seen, owing to corrosion, in typical specimen, but the posterior tibiae not foliaceously dilated.”
</paragraph>
